    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "• CONTINENTAL\n(mementa",
      "The Proud Bird\nCONTINENTAL AIRLINES\nTHE CONTINENTAL AIRLINES McDONNELL DOUG-\nLAS DC-10 (Series 10.) Fuel capacity: 145,201 Ibs. or\n21,671 gallons, or enough to run an automobile 329,085\nmiles — more than 13 trips around the world! Cruising\nspan length: 155 it., 4 ches. Aircral longm 18, Mi., g\nspan length: 155 ft., 4 inches. Aircraft length: 181 ft.,\ninches. Horizontal stabilizer: 71 ft., 2 inches (which is\ngreater than the length of a DC-3 which measures only\n54 feet, 6½ inches.) Vertical stabilizer: 58 ft., 1 inch.\nPowered by: 3 General Electric CF6-6D engines with a\ntotal take-off thrust of 120,000 Ibs.\nPLACE\nSTAMP\nHERE\nA John D. Clayton photograph\n2015166.0577"
    ],
